Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.35,0:00:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, continuing down this path\Nthat Brother Morris started us on,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.36,0:00:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Sanderson\Nis going to develop the theme,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.00,0:00:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“Are You Ready?”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.03,0:00:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ll find out\Nwhat we’re supposed to be ready for
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.57,0:00:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in this talk by Brother Sanderson.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.70,0:00:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And to begin his part,\Nplease look at the monitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.11,0:00:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s a short video clip\Nat the beginning of his part.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.46,0:00:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.60,0:00:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What you just saw occurred
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.60,0:00:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Kostroma region in Russia.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.81,0:00:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The home of a very young couple was raided.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.81,0:01:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And why?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.81,0:01:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Simply because they wanted to worship
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.52,0:01:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the only true and living God, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.39,0:01:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, why is this of interest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.49,0:01:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to all of us who are here today?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.79,0:01:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And why is it that we all need to be ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.20,0:01:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Daniel chapter 11
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.33,0:01:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,foretold of a rivalry between two kings
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.77,0:01:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,—“the king of the north”\Nand “the king of the south.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.27,0:01:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This rivalry has stretched out
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.88,0:01:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,over thousands of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.31,0:01:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and it continues down to our day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.68,0:01:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The king of the north\Nhas manifested a hatred
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.05,0:01:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,for God’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.05,0:01:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, in the 20th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.05,0:01:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and particularly during\Nthe time of the second world war
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.29,0:01:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,when Nazi Germany
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.49,0:01:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,was acting then as the king of the north,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.30,0:01:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we remember\Nthat there was a high concentration
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.20,0:01:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of anointed Christians in the area
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.67,0:02:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,who were being ruled\Nover by Nazi Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.34,0:02:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how did the king\Nof the north treat them?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.11,0:02:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.11,0:02:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They were cruelly persecuted,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.48,0:02:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,sent to concentration camps,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.08,0:02:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and as a result of this, as foretold
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.92,0:02:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in Daniel 11:31,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.05,0:02:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,persecution from that\NGerman king of the north
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.23,0:02:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,resulted in the removal
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.59,0:02:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of what Daniel 11:31 calls
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.13,0:02:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“the constant feature”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.87,0:02:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,—that is, the public preaching activity
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.94,0:02:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of God’s people was suspended
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.57,0:02:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,for a period of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.77,0:02:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what happened\Nwhen the second world war ended?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.28,0:02:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A new king of the north emerged.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.48,0:02:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And who was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.48,0:02:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, of course, it was\Nthe Soviet Union and its allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.95,0:02:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And they too\Ncruelly persecuted God’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.39,0:02:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,They banned our worship of Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.39,0:02:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,they imprisoned many in work camps,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.96,0:03:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and they exiled our brothers to Siberia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.66,0:03:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.67,0:03:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.70,0:03:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,as Daniel 11:34 says,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.71,0:03:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“a little help” was given.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.28,0:03:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what was\Nthat little help that was given?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.55,0:03:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as the Soviet Union collapsed,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.68,0:03:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,bans were lifted\Nacross the former territories
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.49,0:03:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Soviet Union\Nas well as in other lands
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.42,0:03:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that formerly had been\Na part of the Eastern bloc
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.49,0:03:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,behind the Iron Curtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.63,0:03:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what happened then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.00,0:03:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,As we well know, the preaching work
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.90,0:03:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,opened up in that whole region of the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.97,0:03:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and hundreds of thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.71,0:03:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of honesthearted ones
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.71,0:03:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,flocked to Jehovah’s organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.01,0:03:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, brothers,\Nwhere do we find ourselves now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.35,0:03:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as Brother Morris\Nso beautifully explained,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.12,0:04:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,after prayerful consideration,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.79,0:04:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the Governing Body believes that Russia
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.39,0:04:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and its allies today\Nrepresent the king of the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.50,0:04:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And that “pushing” that we are seeing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.40,0:04:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,between the king\Nof the north and the king of the south
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.70,0:04:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,—through these trade wars\Nand cyber espionage
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.07,0:04:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and even through Russia’s seizure\Nof neighboring territories,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.14,0:04:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,such as Crimea—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.35,0:04:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,demonstrate that we are living
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.98,0:04:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,at a time when this prophecy\Nis undergoing fulfillment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.09,0:04:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, is there anything more
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.39,0:04:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Governing Body can say at this time
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.22,0:04:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,about Daniel chapter 11?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.33,0:04:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider together the words
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.60,0:04:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of Daniel 11:41.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.34,0:04:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “He will also enter
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.84,0:04:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,into the land of the Decoration.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.51,0:04:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let’s stop there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.18,0:04:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We have long held
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.18,0:04:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that “the land of the Decoration”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.42,0:05:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,is the spiritual estate of Jehovah’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.92,0:05:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what have we seen
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.12,0:05:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,over the last approximately 18 months\Nin the country of Russia?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.89,0:05:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Please watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.90,0:05:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,On April 20, 2017,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.63,0:05:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Russia’s Supreme Court \Nruled to terminate the activity
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.97,0:05:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of all legal entities \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses in Russia
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.04,0:05:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and to confiscate their property.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.48,0:05:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,On May 25, 2017,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.81,0:05:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Dennis Christensen \Nwas the first brother to be arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.22,0:05:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,following the Supreme Court ban.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.89,0:05:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He has been in detention since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.72,0:05:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,After over 20 court sessions,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.29,0:05:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,his trial continues.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.86,0:05:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,On July 17, 2017,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.60,0:05:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the Supreme Court rejected \Nour appeal against the ban.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.50,0:05:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,On December 14, 2017,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.27,0:06:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,authorities broke \Ninto the Assembly Hall in St. Petersburg
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.48,0:06:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and took control of the property.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.28,0:06:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Legal proceedings to seize hundreds \Nof Kingdom Halls have begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.75,0:06:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The branch property \Nis now officially registered
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.09,0:06:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of the Russian Federation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.16,0:06:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,On December 20, 2017,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.83,0:06:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the Leningrad Regional Court \Nupheld an earlier ruling
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.00,0:06:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that declared \Nthe New World Translation “extremist.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.07,0:06:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And it just continues.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.38,0:06:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look at these faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.15,0:06:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the faces of some\Nof the 71 brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.78,0:06:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,who are presently\Nunder criminal investigation in Russia
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.52,0:06:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,—21 are presently imprisoned
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.83,0:06:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and 15 more are under house arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.00,0:06:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, brothers, what can we say
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.63,0:06:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,about all of these events\Nthat have taken place
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.63,0:07:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,in such a short period of time?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.77,0:07:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, truly, if you’re a student\Nof the history of God’s organization,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.04,0:07:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you can say these events\Nare unprecedented in our history.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.05,0:07:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve never seen a country or a territory
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.95,0:07:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with 175,000 Witnesses of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.89,0:07:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,go under ban.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.92,0:07:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve not seen such\Na large branch seized by a government,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.29,0:07:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as all of our Kingdom Halls
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.43,0:07:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,—and even declaring\Nthe New World Translation “extremist.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.17,0:07:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then, based on all of these events,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.14,0:07:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,what can we say?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.14,0:07:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The Governing Body believes
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.48,0:07:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that these and other actions\Nof Russia and its allies
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.45,0:07:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,constitute a part of the fulfillment
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.45,0:07:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of the king of the north entering
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.29,0:07:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the land of the Decoration.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.05,0:07:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, what can we expect?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.89,0:07:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It would not be surprising
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.29,0:08:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,if Russia and its allies\Ncontinue to persecute God’s people
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.60,0:08:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and that that persecution\Nspreads to other lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.87,0:08:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Already, just a little more than one week ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.31,0:08:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,on September 26, 2018,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.58,0:08:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the Supreme Court\Nof the “Donetsk People’s Republic,”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.68,0:08:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,(that’s one\Nof the breakaway republics from Ukraine)
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.28,0:08:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,declared the religious association
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.02,0:08:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jehovah’s Witnesses to be “extremist.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.12,0:08:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, brothers,\Nthis raises a very important question.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.93,0:08:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this mean
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.06,0:08:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that the attack of Gog of Magog has begun?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.60,0:08:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we’re not ready to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.07,0:08:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.08,0:08:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The annual meeting is not yet over.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.08,0:08:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,By the end of this meeting, you will have
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.35,0:08:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the answer to that important question.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.79,0:08:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But let’s come back to our question:\NAre you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.46,0:09:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we want\Nto be ready when persecution comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.56,0:09:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And quite frankly, brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.76,0:09:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,when ban or opposition comes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.70,0:09:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,on a level like we have seen in Russia,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.24,0:09:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,there are things that we need to know
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.64,0:09:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to be ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.67,0:09:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider four.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.71,0:09:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The first:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.71,0:09:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We must follow direction\Nfrom Jehovah’s organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.08,0:09:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hebrews 13:17 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.18,0:09:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be obedient to those . . .\Ntaking the lead among you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.75,0:09:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.76,0:09:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Jehovah\Nwill use his appointed channel
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.03,0:09:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to provide us\Nwith the direction that we need,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.73,0:09:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can maintain our spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.87,0:09:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And, brothers, it is vital
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.30,0:09:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that we adhere to that direction closely
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.94,0:09:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to preserve our spirituality
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.04,0:09:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and the spirituality of others\Nwho may worship with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.21,0:09:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s the second:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.22,0:10:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t panic,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.72,0:10:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,trust in Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.09,0:10:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and don’t ban yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.96,0:10:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what does Deuteronomy 7:21
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.06,0:10:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,tell us about our opposers?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.70,0:10:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “Do not be struck
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.10,0:10:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“with terror because of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.47,0:10:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“for Jehovah your God is with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.90,0:10:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a great and awe-inspiring God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.24,0:10:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, our opposers
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.24,0:10:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,would love for us to panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.05,0:10:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They would love for us to hear the report
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.08,0:10:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that 21 of our brothers are in prison
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.35,0:10:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and, as a result, become terrified.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.16,0:10:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They would like\Nfor us to stop meeting together
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.76,0:10:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and to stop preaching the good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.79,0:10:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In effect, we could actually ban ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.77,0:10:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But what does Isaiah 28:16 say?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.60,0:10:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “No one
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.61,0:11:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,exercising faith will panic.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.98,0:11:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, brothers, we must not panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.45,0:11:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it’s true, there are 21
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.38,0:11:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of our dear brothers and sisters in Russia
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.82,0:11:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,who are in prison at the present time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.42,0:11:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But, on the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.69,0:11:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,think about how many tens of thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.96,0:11:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of our brothers who are not in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.73,0:11:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, that’s what\Nwe need to focus our minds on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.54,0:11:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And what if we do face arrest
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.54,0:11:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,or imprisonment\Nbecause we faithfully serve
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.81,0:11:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,our God, Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.04,0:11:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we must remember
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.11,0:11:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah will be there to support us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.32,0:11:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I would just love\Nto be able to tell you more,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.99,0:11:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but our brothers in prison in Russia,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.86,0:11:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and many other places,\Nare doing just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.09,0:11:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And why are they doing fine?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.20,0:11:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Jehovah God is with them!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.97,0:11:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no prison wall
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.67,0:12:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that can be built so high, so wide,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.81,0:12:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,or so strong that it can cut us off
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.38,0:12:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,from our heavenly Father, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.20,0:12:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Number three:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.47,0:12:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Protect your spiritual food.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.60,0:12:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers, have a secure place in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.74,0:12:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to hide your Bible\Nand other precious spiritual food,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.64,0:12:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,whether in printed or in electronic form.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.85,0:12:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’re worshipping Jehovah right now
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.78,0:12:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in a country where the work is under ban,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.39,0:12:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,do not leave your spiritual food
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.72,0:12:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,where it can easily\Nbe discovered and taken away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.03,0:13:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Number four:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.10,0:13:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,At 1 Peter 1:22,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.97,0:13:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bible tells us\Nto “love one another intensely from the heart.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.60,0:13:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And our brothers in countries
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.61,0:13:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,where the work\Nis under ban are doing just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.21,0:13:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In many court hearings in Russia,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.64,0:13:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers have risked\Ntheir safety to be in the courtroom
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.98,0:13:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to support their brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.02,0:13:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the brothers were charged
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.49,0:13:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and when they emerged from the courtroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.16,0:13:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,what did those brothers\Nwho were there to support them do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.33,0:13:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Just watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.94,0:14:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you determined, brothers and sisters,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.55,0:14:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to be like our brothers and sisters in Russia
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.25,0:14:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and to stand together\Nas one and support one another
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.18,0:14:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,through the challenging times\Nthat will be coming in the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.93,0:14:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Then remember these practical steps:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.24,0:14:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.61,0:14:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t panic, trust in Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.88,0:14:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and don’t ban yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.15,0:14:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Protect your spiritual food,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.01,0:15:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and support your brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.05,0:15:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Stand together with them as one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.69,0:15:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If we are all determined
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.22,0:15:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to do these practical things right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.99,0:15:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,then, my dear brothers and sisters,\Nyou are ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.28,0:15:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much, Brother Sanderson,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.88,0:15:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,for lighting that fire under us in a good way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.22,0:15:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And also,\Nthank you so much for removing the veil
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.56,0:15:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,concerning ‘the king of the north\Nentering the land of the Decoration.’
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.03,0:15:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we’d like to say, if at all possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.77,0:15:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,do not go to the restroom during this next talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.71,0:16:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.38,0:16:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re going to really miss something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.38,0:16:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So Brother Geoffrey Jackson
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.58,0:16:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to give us the powerful talk now:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.82,0:16:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“They Will Have to Know That I Am Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.71,0:16:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So we’re all thinking\Nof that very important question:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.85,0:16:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Has the attack\Nof Gog of Magog already started?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.02,0:16:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The simple answer is no, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.26,0:16:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can we say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.36,0:16:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you turn with me again \Nto Daniel chapter 11
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.57,0:16:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,—and I’m sure many of us\Nwill be turning there in the next few weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.54,0:16:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking over and over again
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.34,0:16:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,about the significance\Nof these explanations—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.21,0:16:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll notice\Nthat what is happening now
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.38,0:16:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is part of the fulfillment
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.45,0:16:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of Daniel 11:40-43.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.92,0:17:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But you’ll also notice
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.35,0:17:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that it continues on with verses 44 and 45.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.12,0:17:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, these two verses\Napply to something
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.49,0:17:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that will occur\Nafter the start of the great tribulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.43,0:17:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we have understood\Nup to now and continue to understand,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.40,0:17:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the attack of Gog of Magog\Ndoes not occur
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.01,0:17:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,before the outbreak\Nof the great tribulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.31,0:17:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it doesn’t even start
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.48,0:17:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,just as the great tribulation commences
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.65,0:17:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but, rather, it is toward the end\Nof the great tribulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.05,0:17:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do we know\Nabout the attack of Gog of Magog?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.52,0:17:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What will lead up to that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.36,0:17:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s consider\Nthis visual time line to help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.84,0:17:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the centuries, Babylon the Great
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.81,0:17:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,—the world empire of false religion—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.84,0:17:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,has committed spiritual immorality
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.51,0:18:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,with “the kings of the earth.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.18,0:18:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In the near future, \Nthese religious leaders
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.22,0:18:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,could very well have \Na part in causing people
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.89,0:18:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to say that they have attained \Na measure of “peace and security.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.93,0:18:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens next?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.70,0:18:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will put it \Ninto the hearts of the nations
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.43,0:18:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to empower the United Nations \Nto attack Babylon the Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.17,0:18:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The great tribulation starts at this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.24,0:18:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this will not be the attack
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.35,0:18:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of Gog of Magog on God’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.32,0:18:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.15,0:18:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said that \Nthe days of this initial attack
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.36,0:18:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,would be cut short \N“on account of the chosen ones,”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.36,0:18:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that is, \NJesus’ spirit-anointed brothers still on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.30,0:18:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,During all these events, Jehovah’s people
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.04,0:19:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,will continue to enjoy \Nthe spiritual prosperity
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.11,0:19:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that they have experienced \Never since pure worship
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.24,0:19:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,was reestablished in 1919.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.58,0:19:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But whatever respite \Nwe may experience at that time
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.58,0:19:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,will only be the calm before the storm
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.46,0:19:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,—the final storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.56,0:19:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Our spiritual prosperity \Nwill not go unnoticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.07,0:19:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How can it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.47,0:19:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All other religious organizations \Nwill have been destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.44,0:19:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We will be the only ones on this planet
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.14,0:19:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,who are openly serving God.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.75,0:19:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Gog of Magog\N—a coalition of all the nations,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.95,0:19:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, a combination \Nof “the king of the north,”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.29,0:19:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“the king of the south,” \Nand all other nations—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.96,0:19:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,will make plans to attack God’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.70,0:20:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, we will stand out as different
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.73,0:20:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and will appear to be defenseless.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.97,0:20:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,For this reason, \NGog “will devise an evil plan”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.57,0:20:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in a futile attempt \Nto wipe out pure worship from the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.85,0:20:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But in his rage,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.49,0:20:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Gog will not take into consideration
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.06,0:20:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,one vital fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.46,0:20:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,His attack on God’s people
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.86,0:20:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is an attack on Jehovah himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.10,0:20:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What a mistake that will be!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.10,0:20:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Gog will enrage the Sovereign \Nof the universe, Almighty God.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.34,0:20:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This will start the battle of Armageddon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.38,0:20:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,During “the war \Nof the great day of God the Almighty,”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.68,0:20:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will use his heavenly forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.89,0:21:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Included among these \Nwill be all of the 144,000,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.09,0:21:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,who by that time
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.23,0:21:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,will have received their heavenly reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.93,0:21:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, in a spectacular way,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.50,0:21:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will no doubt unleash both natural
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.27,0:21:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and supernatural forces
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.14,0:21:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to protect his loyal servants \Nand eliminate his enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.22,0:21:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That destruction of the wicked
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.48,0:21:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,will usher in the Thousand Year Reign \Nof Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.29,0:21:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,After the final test \Nat the end of the thousand years,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.76,0:21:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,what will be the situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.76,0:21:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,All creation in heaven and on earth
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.27,0:21:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,will be completely united
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.34,0:21:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in the pure worship \Nof our loving heavenly Father, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.94,0:21:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Hallelujah! \NWhat a time that will be!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.50,0:22:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We look forward to the time
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.60,0:22:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,when you’re there\Nand you’ll say, “This is it!”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.68,0:22:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the meantime,\Nas we think to the future and we realize
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.31,0:22:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that Gog of Magog\Nwill attack God’s people
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.28,0:22:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,—this coalition\Nof all the nations of the earth:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.45,0:22:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the king of the north\Nand the king of the south—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.39,0:22:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,should we dread anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.53,0:22:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we be fearful about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.66,0:22:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s turn to the book of Ezekiel,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.83,0:22:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Ezekiel chapter 38,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.17,0:22:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s read\Nfor ourselves the reassurance
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.97,0:22:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that we get\Nfrom these words in Ezekiel 38.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.84,0:22:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s start with verses 18 and 19:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.98,0:23:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘On that day, the day\Nwhen Gog invades the land of Israel,’
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.85,0:23:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“declares the Sovereign Lord Jehovah,\N‘my great rage will flare up.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.82,0:23:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘In my zeal,\Nin the fire of my fury, I will speak;
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.79,0:23:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and in that day\Nthere will be a great earthquake
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.09,0:23:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,in the land of Israel.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.13,0:23:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Then verses 21 to 23:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.17,0:23:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘I will call for a sword against him\Non all my mountains,’
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.44,0:23:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“declares the Sovereign Lord Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.67,0:23:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Every man’s sword\Nwill be against his own brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.24,0:23:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘I will bring my judgment against him
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.84,0:23:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘with pestilence and bloodshed;
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.31,0:23:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and I will rain down\Na torrential downpour
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.02,0:23:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and hailstones and fire
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.29,0:23:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and sulfur on him and on his troops
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.36,0:23:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and on the many peoples with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.32,0:23:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘And I will certainly\Nmagnify myself
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.60,0:23:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and sanctify myself
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.80,0:23:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and make myself known\Nbefore the eyes of many nations;
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.94,0:24:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and they will have to know \Nthat I am Jehovah.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.67,0:24:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren’t those words reassuring?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.44,0:24:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Jehovah will turn his rage
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.05,0:24:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,on Gog of Magog
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.05,0:24:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,because he upholds his name
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.99,0:24:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and protects his name people.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.12,0:24:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have nothing to dread.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.79,0:24:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the past few years,\Nyou’ve probably noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.93,0:24:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that at a number\Nof the annual meetings,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.10,0:24:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ve had some clarifications
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.23,0:24:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with regard to the prophecy of Ezekiel.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.40,0:24:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn’t it be nice if we had\Nall those clarifications
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.24,0:24:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,together in one location?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.67,0:24:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you’ll be pleased\Nto know that ten years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.85,0:24:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in the year 2008,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.21,0:24:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the Governing Body\Ncommissioned the Writing Committee
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.42,0:24:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to start preparing a book\Non the prophecy of Ezekiel.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.76,0:24:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, in the meantime,\Nthe text of the book of Ezekiel
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.56,0:24:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,was refined and revised
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.50,0:25:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and many, many things\Nhave happened on the world scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.80,0:25:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we have to wait another ten years?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.50,0:25:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not even\Ngoing to go down that track with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.47,0:25:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll be pleased to know
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.47,0:25:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that today we’re releasing\Na brand new publication:
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.41,0:25:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Pure Worship of Jehovah\N—Restored at Last!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.20,0:25:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you all seem\Nvery excited about this;
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.64,0:25:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,all you saw is the front cover.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.14,0:25:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we expect\Nwhen we open the pages
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.68,0:25:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of this new publication?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.88,0:25:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s take a sneak preview
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.28,0:25:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,of what you’ll find in this publication.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.79,0:25:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, you’ll be happy to see
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.86,0:26:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that it contains\Nall the recent clarifications
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.79,0:26:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that we’ve had with regard\Nto our understanding of the book of Ezekiel.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.56,0:26:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can say
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.27,0:26:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,there are a few more\Nclarifications as well in this book,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.67,0:26:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Pure Worship of Jehovah\N—Restored at Last!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.44,0:26:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,On pages 238 to 240,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.35,0:26:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you will find a summary of clarifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.65,0:26:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So no doubt most of us\Nwill be turning there first
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.45,0:26:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to read through those.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.46,0:26:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Numerous charts and time lines\Nappear throughout the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.29,0:26:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The teaching boxes help us gain
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.93,0:26:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,a deeper understanding of Ezekiel
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.33,0:26:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and his writings;
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.47,0:26:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,these are designed to help us
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.67,0:26:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to get the overall background
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.77,0:26:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and setting of these prophecies.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.38,0:26:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Scattered throughout this book
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.21,0:26:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,are beautiful illustrations
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.08,0:27:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,—illustrations that bring to life
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.09,0:27:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the fascinating prophecies
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.62,0:27:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that Ezekiel was inspired to record—
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.59,0:27:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,all for our benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.76,0:27:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,As you meditate\Non these instructive pieces of art,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.56,0:27:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you will no doubt start\Nto visualize for yourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.40,0:27:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the exciting visions
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.90,0:27:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and the amazing things
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.21,0:27:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that Ezekiel describes\Nin this prophetic book.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.43,0:27:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Lett will tell you\Nwhen you’ll receive your copies.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.80,0:27:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I know all of you are thinking\Nat this point: ‘OK, you can go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.77,0:27:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We’d like to hear\Nwhen we’re going to get them.’
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.71,0:27:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But before we finish this part,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.51,0:28:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,we’d like to mention
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.51,0:28:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that in the digital version\Nof this publication,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.92,0:28:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s a new feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.12,0:28:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There are 22 chapters in the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.16,0:28:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the beginning of each chapter,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.76,0:28:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s a little video clip\Nthat introduces the chapter.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.03,0:28:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And these video clips
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.10,0:28:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,are presented by either members\Nof the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.20,0:28:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,or helpers to the Governing Body.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.64,0:28:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to see\Na little summary of some of those?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.05,0:28:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Pure Worship of Jehovah\N—Restored At Last!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.79,0:28:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What spiritual gems will we find in this book?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.73,0:28:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Will there be clarifications of understanding?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.56,0:28:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.90,0:28:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Will we see beautiful illustrations\Nof vivid prophetic visions?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.47,0:28:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.97,0:29:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The better you understand Bible principles,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.64,0:29:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the greater will be\Nyour desire to reject Satan’s traps
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.41,0:29:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and to give Jehovah exclusive, pure worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.51,0:29:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do the faces of a man, a lion, a bull,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.08,0:29:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and an eagle especially reflect\NJehovah’s strength and mightiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.12,0:29:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What does the chariot\Nthat Ezekiel saw represent,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.59,0:29:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and how do we know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.83,0:29:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What promises of restoration\Ndid Jehovah make through Ezekiel,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.43,0:29:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and how have they been fulfilled\Non true Christians during the last days?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.00,0:29:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we learn from Ezekiel’s prophecy
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.21,0:29:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,about Jerusalem’s destruction?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.68,0:29:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,How does Ezekiel’s vision of the man
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.55,0:29:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,with the secretary’s inkhorn\Nhighlight Jehovah’s mercy?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.85,0:29:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What lies ahead for false religion,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.05,0:29:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and what action should we take now?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.06,0:29:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah asked the prophet Ezekiel\Nto do some strange things.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.13,0:30:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But they conveyed an important message\Nthat has meaning for us today.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.57,0:30:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you enjoy picturing yourself\Nand your loved ones in Paradise?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.34,0:30:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A study of Ezekiel’s visionary river
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.34,0:30:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,will help you to make\Nthat picture even more vivid.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.68,0:30:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true that understanding Bible prophecy
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.85,0:30:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,requires humility, hard work, and holy spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.09,0:30:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But the rewards are worth the effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.22,0:30:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The material you’re\Nabout to discuss will give you courage,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.99,0:30:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and it will help you\Nto do your part in upholding pure worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.03,0:30:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The better you understand this material,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.83,0:30:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the stronger your determination will be
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.84,0:30:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to give Jehovah pure worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.94,0:30:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s our hope that what you’ve learned\Nfrom the Pure Worship book
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.51,0:30:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,will strengthen your determination
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.01,0:30:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to give Jehovah\Nwhat he so richly deserves
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.18,0:30:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,—your exclusive worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.00,0:31:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,May this new publication
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.57,0:31:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,enhance our appreciation for pure worship,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.87,0:31:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,may it continue to build within us
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.67,0:31:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,a feeling of urgency with regard\Nto the times in which we’re living,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.94,0:31:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and may it help us to have a longing
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.81,0:31:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,for the time when all creation\Nin heaven and on earth
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.05,0:31:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,will not only know Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.15,0:31:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but love and worship him\Nfor all eternity!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.49,0:31:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What a powerful part, Brother Jackson!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.83,0:31:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And we thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.83,0:31:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And thank you for removing the veil
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.40,0:32:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,from Gog, a coalition of nations,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.17,0:32:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,including the king of the north\Nand the king of the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.84,0:32:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But now,\Nregarding our wonderful publication
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.41,0:32:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that Brother Jackson told you about
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.35,0:32:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,—and he put the pressure on me;
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.72,0:32:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve got to give you\Nthe right announcement this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.95,0:32:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so here’s the right announcement—
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.82,0:32:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pure Worship book in English
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.39,0:32:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,will be made available on jw.org,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.09,0:32:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Watchtower ONLINE LIBRARY,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.70,0:32:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and JW Library®
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.70,0:32:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,on Monday, October 8, 2018.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.64,0:32:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So Monday is going to be a big day.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.64,0:32:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If you will be making use
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.61,0:32:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of a hard copy of this publication,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.71,0:32:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,one copy of the printed edition
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.08,0:32:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,will be available after the program
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.28,0:32:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,at the various annual meeting locations,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.45,0:32:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,including the main lobby of your complex
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.72,0:32:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,for those watching\Nfrom their personal rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.63,0:33:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Additional printed copies\Nmay be requested
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.63,0:33:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,through the congregations,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.80,0:33:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,including the large-print edition.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.90,0:33:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we move to our final talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.57,0:33:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and Brother David Splane\Nis going to give us this comforting talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.18,0:33:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do Not Be Anxious, for I Am Your God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.18,0:33:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah knows\Nwe need this comforting talk
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.69,0:33:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,after the powerful preceding trilogy
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.22,0:33:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we just heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.23,0:33:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So Brother Splane, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.78,0:33:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I told some of the brothers that my job
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.95,0:33:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is to cheer you up after the preceding talks.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.79,0:33:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, bad things happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.60,0:33:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They happen to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.93,0:33:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and they happen to those we love.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.07,0:34:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So here’s the question:
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.57,0:34:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it possible to remain calm
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.88,0:34:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,when it seems that our life\Nis being turned upside down?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.38,0:34:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answer is yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.48,0:34:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And let’s consider\Nfour reasons why we say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.95,0:34:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is simple\Nbecause all of these reasons
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.59,0:34:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,are contained in one Bible verse
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.79,0:34:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,—Isaiah 41:10—
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.80,0:34:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s Isaiah chapter 41.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.37,0:34:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can’t find Isaiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.14,0:34:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,try “Isaiah” 41:10
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.45,0:34:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,—four reasons why we can be calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.85,0:34:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It says:\N“Do not be afraid, for I am with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.85,0:34:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not be anxious, for I am your God.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.59,0:34:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will fortify you, yes, I will help you,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.50,0:35:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will really hold on to you
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.50,0:35:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,with my right hand of righteousness.”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.17,0:35:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You can leave your Bibles open.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.17,0:35:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re going to be returning to this book,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.71,0:35:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re going to be staying\Nin Isaiah for the duration of this talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.35,0:35:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, more than 100 years\Nafter these words were written down,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.35,0:35:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,a very bad thing happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.89,0:35:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The king of Babylon\Ninvaded the city of Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.89,0:35:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Bible says of him\Nthat he felt no compassion
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.83,0:35:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,for young man or virgin, old or infirm.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.47,0:35:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He burned down the house of the true God,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.34,0:35:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,tore down the wall of Jerusalem,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.47,0:35:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,burned all its fortified towers with fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.94,0:35:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and destroyed everything of value.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.11,0:35:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there were survivors.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.52,0:35:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Bear in mind,\Nwe’re not talking about our friends
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.09,0:35:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel, Ezekiel, Shadrach,\NMeshach, and Abednego.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.96,0:36:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They were already in Babylon,\Nbut there were survivors.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.73,0:36:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But can you picture in your mind’s eye
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.70,0:36:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,what was happening to the survivors?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.90,0:36:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Just try to picture it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.37,0:36:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There they are bound in chains,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.67,0:36:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,being dragged through the rubble
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.14,0:36:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,—the smoldering rubble—\Nof the holy city.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.31,0:36:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see them?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.42,0:36:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see them pass a widow
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.92,0:36:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,who is cradling\Nthe lifeless body of her only son?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.32,0:36:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now a soldier approaches,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.33,0:36:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and he orders the woman\Nto drop her son and to get on her feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.80,0:36:43.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But she can’t;\Nshe just can’t let go of her son, her precious son.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.67,0:36:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,With one stroke, the soldier ends her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.41,0:36:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And those looking on\Nwonder what fate awaits them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.85,0:36:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can imagine\Nfaithful ones among them
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.85,0:37:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,repeating the words of Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.59,0:37:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,by means of Isaiah,\Nover and over again:
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.32,0:37:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Do not be anxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.86,0:37:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Do not be anxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.60,0:37:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I am your God.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.80,0:37:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I will fortify you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.67,0:37:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I will hold on to you.’
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.04,0:37:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, those same words\Nhave been a source of great encouragement
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.74,0:37:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jehovah’s people throughout the ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.84,0:37:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And they can be a source\Nof strength for us today.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.15,0:37:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s take a closer look at Isaiah 41:10
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.49,0:37:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and discuss the four reasons
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.65,0:37:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,why we needn’t be overly anxious
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.19,0:37:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,when bad things happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.29,0:37:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So keep your Bibles open to Isaiah,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.40,0:37:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s look at the first reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.90,0:37:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What does Jehovah say?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.23,0:37:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“For I am with you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.90,0:37:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what’s the first word in that phrase?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.54,0:37:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“I.”
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.54,0:38:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah doesn’t say:\N‘Don’t be anxious because you’re real smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.88,0:38:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll figure something out.’
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.88,0:38:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.88,0:38:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We needn’t be anxious if Jehovah is with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.05,0:38:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If we put our trust completely in Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.46,0:38:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s the very best way to calm our fears,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.46,0:38:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s been repeated to us\Nduring the program of this convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.03,0:38:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, isn’t Jehovah\Njust interested in the big picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.27,0:38:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Jehovah really interested\Nin you and your problems?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.27,0:38:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He assures the Israelites that he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.98,0:38:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Just turn to Isaiah 43,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.32,0:38:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and notice what he says in verse 2
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.12,0:38:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,(he’s speaking to you):
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.36,0:38:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“When you pass through the waters,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.19,0:38:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will be with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.33,0:38:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“and through the rivers,\Nthey will not flood over you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.23,0:38:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“When you walk through the fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.37,0:38:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“you will not be scorched,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.37,0:39:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,nor will the flame singe you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.21,0:39:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Jehovah doesn’t say\Nthere won’t be challenges.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.38,0:39:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There will be rivers,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.48,0:39:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah will not allow\Nthose rivers to flood over us.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.45,0:39:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There will be fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.95,0:39:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah will not allow the flames
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.02,0:39:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to consume us.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.06,0:39:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has the power over fire and water,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.43,0:39:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah says that he will be with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.07,0:39:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So we will leave every trial
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.87,0:39:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,—we will go out of every trial—
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.87,0:39:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,with our integrity intact\Nwith the help of Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.91,0:39:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah does something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.91,0:39:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah can also help quiet our fears
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.11,0:39:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we’re not afraid\Nof the trials that beset us.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.05,0:39:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this was evident\Nin the case of a sister named Yoshiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.06,0:39:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctor gave her very bad news.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.83,0:39:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,She had only a few months to live,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.20,0:40:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah was with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.70,0:40:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What did He do?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.70,0:40:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Did He provide a miraculous cure?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.97,0:40:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.17,0:40:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Her daughter said:
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.21,0:40:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“We were impressed\Nwith how calm Mom was.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.51,0:40:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We truly saw\Nthat Jehovah gave her inner peace.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.22,0:40:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I’m sure you could relate\Nmany, many experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.75,0:40:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,when Jehovah has given you\Nthat same peace of God
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.32,0:40:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that has helped you to endure trials.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.89,0:40:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let’s note the second reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.26,0:40:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back to Isaiah 41:10,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.13,0:40:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s note the second reason \Nwhy we can remain calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.30,0:40:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He says:\N“Do not be anxious,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.17,0:40:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,for I am your God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.61,0:40:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in this verse,\Nthe word for “be anxious”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.58,0:40:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,conveys the thought of looking\Nover your shoulder and expecting trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.75,0:40:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,or being in a constant state of alarm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.19,0:40:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, is that really helpful?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.35,0:41:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It reminds me\Nof the American writer Mark Twain;
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.46,0:41:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,he said, ‘I’m an old man
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.23,0:41:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and I have known many troubles,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.50,0:41:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but most of them never happened.’
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.33,0:41:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s really true, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.10,0:41:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So often the things we expect to happen
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.27,0:41:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,—the things we worry about—\Ndon’t happen at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.74,0:41:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what’s the point?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.91,0:41:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing is gained by trying to imagine\Nwhat form persecution might take
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.51,0:41:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or how we might react under a certain trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.02,0:41:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.02,0:41:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we know our God,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.39,0:41:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and we know what Jehovah can do for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.96,0:41:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.96,0:41:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of his past record.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.09,0:41:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve seen how he\Nhas already intervened in our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.27,0:41:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s done it before, and he can do it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.54,0:41:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember the song?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.57,0:41:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“You promised him in prayer to do his will;
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.11,0:41:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,he helped you then, and he will help you still.”
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.18,0:41:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is so true.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.18,0:41:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, think about the first trial
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.18,0:41:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that you encountered\Nwhen you were coming into the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.22,0:42:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it was your relatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.55,0:42:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You were studying,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.55,0:42:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and you were wondering\Nhow you were going to break the news
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.66,0:42:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to your relatives that you\Nwere studying with Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.66,0:42:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And you begged Jehovah\Nto give you just the right words
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.03,0:42:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you’d know\Nhow to break the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.20,0:42:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn’t go well.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.14,0:42:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And you felt as if you\Nwere walking through fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.61,0:42:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But did the fire consume you?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.75,0:42:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well no, look at you;\Nyou’re here.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.28,0:42:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah helped you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.42,0:42:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave you the peace of God,\Nand he helped you to endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.05,0:42:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you have\Na better relationship with your relatives
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.62,0:42:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as you don’t talk about the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.70,0:42:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He helped you then,\Nand he will help you still.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.90,0:42:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, looking back,\Nyou might not see that as a very difficult test
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.64,0:42:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because since that time,\Nyou’ve been through a lot worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.84,0:42:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was a test nevertheless,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.31,0:43:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and you passed that test successfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.51,0:43:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And so when you went\Nthrough much worse later,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.78,0:43:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you were able to encounter that test
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.78,0:43:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and pass it because your faith was stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.99,0:43:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has built your faith little by little.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.39,0:43:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Jehovah\Nwon’t always remove our problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.26,0:43:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have a problem
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.60,0:43:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and there’s something\Nyou can do about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.00,0:43:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,then pray for wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.30,0:43:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If there’s nothing\Nyou can do about the problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.04,0:43:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,pray for peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.11,0:43:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But in any case, pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.98,0:43:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The next best thing to solving a problem
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.91,0:43:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is not to be worried about the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.02,0:43:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let’s go back to verse 10
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.68,0:43:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and consider the third assurance\Nthat we get from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.49,0:43:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He says:\N“I will fortify you,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.93,0:43:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, I will help you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.83,0:43:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what does that word “fortify” mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.43,0:43:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It means to make us stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.40,0:44:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this morning, we’ve heard a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.27,0:44:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that could be scary on some levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.17,0:44:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And we might catch ourselves saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.38,0:44:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I don’t think I’d do very well under persecution.’
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.15,0:44:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s wrong with that statement?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.35,0:44:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I don’t think I would do well
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.22,0:44:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,under persecution.’
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.26,0:44:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is not in the picture,\Nand yet he should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.03,0:44:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Who says we have to face persecution alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.87,0:44:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah says that he is going to fortify us.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.07,0:44:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He is going to give us the inner strength\Nthat we didn’t know we had
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.91,0:44:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,because we don’t have it\Nif we’re not facing persecution.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.01,0:44:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You may not be strong enough
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.08,0:44:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to encounter persecution now\Nif you’re not going through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.12,0:44:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But when the time comes\N—and it will come—
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.02,0:44:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will give you the strength you need.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.46,0:44:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He says:\N‘I will fortify you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.46,0:45:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I will make you strong.’
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.30,0:45:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s consider the last phrase in verse 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.00,0:45:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah says:\N“I will really hold on to you
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.74,0:45:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,with my right hand of righteousness.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.97,0:45:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, The Watchtower of July 2016\Nclarified this verse for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.85,0:45:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We used to often think of ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.88,0:45:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,walking hand in hand with Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.42,0:45:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but that’s not really what he’s talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.92,0:45:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we know?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.46,0:45:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it’s because of what he says in verse 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.83,0:45:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It says:\N“For I, Jehovah your God,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.00,0:45:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,am grasping your right hand.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.53,0:45:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But what does he say at the end of verse 10?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.20,0:45:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will really hold on to you\Nwith my right hand of righteousness.”
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.21,0:45:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If we were walking side by side with Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.75,0:45:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,our right hand would be in his left hand
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.05,0:45:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,or our left hand would be in his right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.78,0:45:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But he says,\N‘No, I will hold on to you with my right hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.29,0:45:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and I will hold on to your right hand.’
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.29,0:46:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what is the picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.66,0:46:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re down; and you can’t get up;
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.03,0:46:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah God extends his right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.40,0:46:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And what do you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.87,0:46:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t just lie there.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.77,0:46:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Extend your right hand;\Nallow Jehovah to help you to get up.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.58,0:46:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you’re battling depression right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.81,0:46:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Or perhaps you’ve lost\Na cherished privilege of service,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.02,0:46:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and you just can’t get over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.15,0:46:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Extend your right hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.72,0:46:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and allow Jehovah to help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.22,0:46:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe he’ll use an elder\Nas his right-hand man.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.03,0:46:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But he’s going to use somebody to help you
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.13,0:46:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,if only you are willing to accept
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.63,0:46:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the help that Jehovah will give.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.40,0:46:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there they are:
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.40,0:46:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Four reasons why we can keep calm\Nno matter what the future holds.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.04,0:46:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah says: “I am with you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.98,0:46:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He says: “I am your God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.28,0:47:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will fortify you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.02,0:47:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And “I will really hold on to you\Nwith my right hand.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.86,0:47:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful assurance that is!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.69,0:47:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re going to have a whole year
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.89,0:47:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to consider these words in depth
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.50,0:47:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because part of this text,\Nas you have probably guessed,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.27,0:47:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,constitutes our yeartext for the year 2019.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.97,0:47:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And here it is:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.98,0:47:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not be anxious, for I am your God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.68,0:47:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much, Brother Splane,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.68,0:47:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,for that balsam of Gilead,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.85,0:47:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and also we appreciate
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.06,0:47:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that yeartext, Isaiah 41:10.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.13,0:48:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful scripture\Nwe’ll focus on during 2019!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.20,0:48:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But now I’ve been apportioned five minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.70,0:48:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,for some concluding comments.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.57,0:48:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And even though we’re overtime,\NI’m going to take my five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.84,0:48:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll probably hear about it later, though,\Nfrom the Governing Body brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.29,0:48:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I leave out of here\Nreal quick after the program,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.33,0:48:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll know what the problem is.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.50,0:48:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Near the beginning of our program,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.60,0:48:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we focused just for a few minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.80,0:48:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,on appreciating our spiritual paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.61,0:48:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And to substantiate\Nhow truly paradisaic it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.65,0:48:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we made comparisons\Nbetween that original Paradise
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.22,0:48:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and our spiritual paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.39,0:49:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And we discussed seven similarities.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.62,0:49:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, just to review,\Nour spiritual paradise,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.19,0:49:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,like the garden of Eden,\Nexists on a land.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.06,0:49:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It is filled with beautiful plants and trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.43,0:49:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It has abundant food and refreshing water.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.77,0:49:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It has many harmless animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.21,0:49:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It needs maintenance,\Nand it has boundaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.95,0:49:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But just briefly,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.98,0:49:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s discuss one more\N—an eighth similarity.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.12,0:49:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Our spiritual paradise
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.02,0:49:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is expanding
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.42,0:49:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to embrace more and more people.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.93,0:49:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Originally, Jehovah intended\Nthe garden of Eden to expand—didn’t he?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.86,0:49:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that Jehovah\Ntold him in Genesis 1:28:
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.44,0:49:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“Become fruitful and become many,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.87,0:49:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,fill the earth and subdue it.”
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.34,0:49:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So as Adam and Eve had children
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.65,0:50:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and as their children had children,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.98,0:50:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the garden of Eden would become\Ntoo small eventually—wouldn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.18,0:50:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It would have to grow;\Nit would have to expand bigger and bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.82,0:50:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, the east would meet the west;
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.83,0:50:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the north would meet the south;
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.89,0:50:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the planet Earth\Nwould become the garden of Eden.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.16,0:50:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, we know that\Nthat original procedure Jehovah had in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.74,0:50:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you could say, was blocked\Nby the rebellion in the garden of Eden.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.57,0:50:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, Jehovah’s original purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.31,0:50:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for the earth to be a paradise\Nlike the garden of Eden
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.28,0:50:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly will be accomplished.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.38,0:50:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, here is the point:
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.45,0:50:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as Jehovah intended\Nthe garden of Eden to expand,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.32,0:50:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,he desires our spiritual paradise to expand
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.19,0:50:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,—to embrace more and more people.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.99,0:50:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And that definitely is happening\N—isn’t it?—
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.23,0:50:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,as all of us focus on making disciples.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.83,0:50:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And right now our spiritual paradise
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.54,0:51:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,embraces some eight\Nand a half million sheeplike individuals.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.97,0:51:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And only Jehovah\Nknows how many more will come into it
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.18,0:51:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,before the great tribulation begins
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.18,0:51:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,as all of us do our best to make disciples.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.02,0:51:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah expects us to do that\N—to do our very best
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.59,0:51:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to expand this spiritual paradise,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.83,0:51:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,this wonderful,\Nbeautiful place where we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.30,0:51:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And this will happen until,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.40,0:51:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we know, the spiritual paradise\Nwill go through the great tribulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.34,0:51:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And then resurrected ones\Nand ones born in the new world
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.07,0:51:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,will come into this spiritual paradise
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.21,0:51:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,if they exercise faith in Jehovah’s provisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.18,0:51:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But there will be many that’ll do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.18,0:51:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ll come into this spiritual paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.22,0:51:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This will happen over and over again,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.32,0:51:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,until the spiritual paradise
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.32,0:51:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,will cover the entire planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.76,0:51:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And this exquisite paradise
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.19,0:51:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,will actually be more beautiful,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.76,0:52:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,more exquisite, than the literal Paradise
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.47,0:52:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that will coexist with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.94,0:52:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So there we have eight similarities
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.84,0:52:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,between the original Paradise\Nand our spiritual paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.11,0:52:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And we never want to take it for granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.31,0:52:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we touched\Non a little bit in the beginning,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.08,0:52:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we never want to allow Satan
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.59,0:52:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to do what he did to Adam and Eve.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.32,0:52:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He got them out\Nof their wonderful place, didn’t he?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.42,0:52:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he’s trying\Nto lure us out of the boundaries
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.56,0:52:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of our wonderful,\Nexquisite spiritual paradise,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.00,0:52:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but we are not going to let him do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.27,0:52:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re determined
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.44,0:52:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that we’re going\Nto help others that are of honest heart
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.87,0:52:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to join us in this spiritual paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.51,0:52:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And this wonderful annual meeting
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.35,0:52:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,has truly helped us in this regard.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.75,0:52:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I know all of us are so happy we were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.52,0:52:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, there are many things\Nyou could do on a Saturday,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.62,0:53:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but we did the best thing\Nwe could have done this Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.09,0:53:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We were here\Nat this wonderful annual meeting.
